text:
The hands still clasp the lingering glass;  
The lips I longed to cool, alas!  
Are now so needlessly cold,

source_text:
The hands still hug the tardy glass;
The lips I would have cooled, alas!
Are so superfluous cold,

text:
“An embroidery of flowers, which enriched
The grassy garment of the desert, glowed,
Unmindful of the chariot’s rapid course;

source_text:
‘Embroidery of flowers, that did enhance
The grassy vesture of the desert, played,
Forgetful of the chariot’s swift advance;
